- "stands out like a beacon" refers to the top-rated course;
- "shining with the highest average rating and glowing reviews" refers to the highest average rating and the total number of feedback entries;
- "the guiding star, the top instructor" refers to the instructor with the highest-rated course.

- 'Blooming in the year 2023' refers to courses that have offerings starting between January 1, 2023, and December 31, 2023;
- 'Lasting longer than 20 hours' refers to courses with a duration greater than 20 hours;
- 'Higher average fee' means the average fee for the course is greater than the average fee across all courses.

- 'course format' can be thought of as different types of educational settings, such as online, offline, or hybrid;
- 'course language' refers to the language in which the course is taught, such as English, Spanish, or Mandarin;
- 'total fees' represent the sum of all fees for courses that share the same format and language;
- 'most valuable to least valuable' implies sorting the results in descending order by total fees.

- "blossoms" metaphorically refers to courses;
- "young minds" metaphorically refers to students;
- "wise sages" metaphorically refers to instructors;
- The "academic garden" is a metaphorical representation of the educational institution.

- "Blossoms of 'Weded Planning'" refers to courses with "Wedding Planning" in their names;
- "Tended to by more than one American student" indicates that the course has more than one active enrollment from students in the USA;
- "Status of their nurturing" refers to the status of the enrollments, specifically those that are active.

- 'Wedding Planning' is a specific course offered in the educational institution;
- 'John Doe' is the name of a specific instructor;
- 'active' enrollment status indicates that the students are currently enrolled in the course.

- "Blossomed" refers to students who have successfully completed the course;
- "Percentage of successful completions" is calculated as the number of completed enrollments divided by the total number of enrollments, multiplied by 100;
- "Stands tall" implies the course with the highest completion rate.

- "A fleeting moment" refers to a duration greater than 10 hours;
- "Threshold of excellence" refers to an average grade greater than 80;
- "Nurturing these blossoms" refers to the number of students and assignments contributing to the course.

- 'Certified Wedding and Event Planner' is a specific course name;
- 'assignment_type' can include various types like 'quiz', 'project', 'essay';
- 'grade' represents the score received for each assignment;
- 'No Assignment' and a grade of 0 are used for students who have no submissions.

- "blossoms" refers to students;
- "thrived above the average" refers to students with an average grade higher than the overall average;
- "guardians" refers to instructors;
- "nurtured more saplings" refers to instructors who have more assignments than the average number of assignments;
- "plots" refers to courses;
- "most visited by eager learners" refers to courses with more enrolled students than the average number of enrolled students.

- "shining star" refers to the top-performing student;
- "leading the way" means having the highest total grade;
- "total grade" is the sum of all grades received for submissions in the course.

- "Certified" students are those who have completed the course and received a formal recognition of their achievement;
- "Average rating" is a measure of student satisfaction, typically on a scale from 1 to 5;
- "Total payments" represent the revenue generated from student enrollments in the course.

- "recent offering" refers to the most recent start date of the course offering;
- "latest feedback" refers to the most recent feedback date provided by students;
- "newest material" refers to the most recent material ID for the course;
- "most experienced instructor" refers to the instructor with the highest years of experience for the course.

- The highest-rated course is determined by the average rating given by students;
- A completed course means the enrollment status is 'completed';
- The total payment is the sum of all payments made by a student for a course.
